  "notes": "Manx (Gaelg). Isle of Man. Last native speaker (Ned Maddrell) died 1974. Revival since 1970s; ~1,800 speakers (est. 2020). English-based orthography (unlike Irish/Scots Gaelic). Simplified mutation system vs. Irish/Scots Gaelic. Refs: Thomson (1992), Broderick (1984).",
